            <div type="translation">
                <p>'... of the son of <foreign xml:lang="sga">Coirpre</foreign> son of <foreign xml:lang="sga">Amalgaid</foreign>'?</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Little can be said about the unintelligible reading of the first (SE) angle. With regard to the second (NE) angle, the father’s name (possibly <foreign xml:lang="sga">Amalgaid</foreign>, or the like) was previously identified by Macalister and others with a king of Connacht who died between 440 and 450 AD but the linguistic forms in the inscription rather suggest a late sixth or even early seventh century date. However, since <foreign xml:lang="sga">Amalgaid</foreign> could be the grandfather of the commemorated person, a 6th-century date isn’t beyond possibility.</p>
            </div>
